# Project: [Your App Name]

## Stack
- Framework: Flutter / Dart
- Backend: Custom REST API
- No testing required at this stage

## Project Structure
```
lib/
  core/                      # Reusable infrastructure — zero app-specific knowledge
    atomic_state/
      atom.dart              # Atom<T> — ValueNotifier with emit() and call()
      async_atom.dart        # AsyncAtom<T> — Atom<Result<T>> initialized as Idle()
      result.dart            # Result<T> sealed class
      auth_state.dart        # AuthState sealed hierarchy
    helpers.dart             # Helper static utility class + debugLog, gradeCoinSymbol
    global_atoms.dart        # authState + keyboardOpened — app-wide atoms
    env.dart                 # Env configuration
    extensions.dart          # App-wide extension helpers
    entity_adapter.dart      # Entity adapter helpers
    cache/                   # Local storage — AppCache + SharedPreferences singleton
    http/                    # APIRequest + ResponseInterceptor + toResult<T>
    localization/            # LocalizationService + localeAtom
    local_auth/              # AppLifecycleService + BiometricAuthService
    notifications/           # OneSignal infrastructure + NotificationRouter
    form_builder/            # API-driven form widgets
    ui/                      # DesignTokens, UIKText, AppButton, UIKBottomSheet
    auth_builder.dart        # Auth side effects — never routing
  controllers/               # One file per feature — controller class + its atoms
  data/                      # One file per feature — service class only
  models/                    # One file per model — plain Dart data classes
  views/                     # One folder per feature
  widgets/                   # Global reusable widgets shared across features
  l10n/                      # Localisation arb files + generated output
  router.dart                # GoRouter — app-specific, lives at root not core/
  main.dart
```

## File placement rules
Given a feature called **rewards**:
| What | Where |
|---|---|
| Data model | `lib/models/reward_model.dart` |
| API service | `lib/data/rewards_service.dart` |
| Controller + atoms | `lib/controllers/rewards_controller.dart` |
| Main screen | `lib/views/rewards/rewards_screen.dart` |
| Feature-specific widgets | `lib/views/rewards/widgets/reward_card.dart` |
| Shared/global widgets | `lib/widgets/` |

**Never** put feature-specific widgets in `lib/widgets/` — they belong in the feature's own `widgets/` folder.
**Never** put models inside `data/` — all models live in `lib/models/`.
**Never** create a `lib/pages/` or `lib/screens/` folder — all screens live in `lib/views/`.

## Architecture
```
View  →  Controller  →  Service (data/)  →  API
              ↓
         atom.emit(result)
              ↓
         View rebuilds via atom()
```

- **Views** call controller methods and render atoms — nothing else
- **Controllers** plain Dart classes — orchestrate service calls, manage atom state, caching. Atom lives in the same file.
- **Services** extend `APIRequest`, return `Result<T>` — no logic, just HTTP
- **Atoms** are the single source of truth — `Atom<T>` for local state, `AsyncAtom<T>` for async data
- **`core/`** contains reusable infrastructure with zero app-specific knowledge — if you could copy it unchanged to another Flutter project, it belongs in `core/`. If it imports any view, model, or feature, it lives outside.
- **`router.dart`** lives at `lib/router.dart` — it's app-specific infrastructure, not reusable core

## Core Primitives

### Atom<T>
Local/UI state. Use `emit()` to update, call directly as widget to render.
```dart
final isSelected = Atom(false);
isSelected.emit(true);
isSelected((_) => const SelectedIndicator())
isSelected((_) => const SelectedIndicator(), fallback: const UnselectedIndicator())
```
Only use with `Atom<bool>`, `Atom<String>`, `Atom<List>`. Assert catches misuse in debug mode.

### AsyncAtom<T>
Async/remote data. Wraps `Result<T>`, initializes as `Idle()`. Call directly as widget.
```dart
final rewards = AsyncAtom<List<RewardModel>>();
rewards.emit(Loading());
rewards.emit(result);
rewards(success: RewardsList.new, failure: ErrorText.new)
```

### Widget convention
Widgets used as constructor references must accept the value as a single positional argument:
```dart
class RewardsList extends StatelessWidget {
  const RewardsList(this.rewards, {super.key});
  final List<RewardModel> rewards;
}
// NOT: const RewardsList({super.key, required this.rewards})
```

### Result<T>
```dart
Idle()            // before any action
Loading()         // in progress
Success(value)    // data returned
Failure(message)  // something went wrong
Empty()           // request succeeded but no data
```
- Never use `Atom<Result<T>>` directly — always use `AsyncAtom<T>`
- Use `result.errorMessage` to extract error string without casting

## Auth State
```dart
sealed class AuthState {}
class Initial extends AuthState {}       // unknown — triggers checkAuth()
class Authenticated extends AuthState {}
class Unauthenticated extends AuthState {}
class AuthErrorState extends AuthState { final String message; }
```
- Interceptor automatically emits `Unauthenticated()` on 401-style responses
- Never manually check for auth errors in services or controllers

## AuthBuilder & Session Management
`AuthBuilder` wraps the entire app. Listens to `authState`, handles routing, notifications, atom resets.

Auth check flow:
```
App starts / comes to foreground
  → authState.emit(Initial())
  → AuthRepository().checkAuth()  ← only called on Initial
  → emits Authenticated or Unauthenticated
  → handles routing / notifications / _resetAtoms()
```

`_resetAtoms()` resets all feature `AsyncAtom`s to `Idle()` on logout.
No manual registration is required — `AsyncAtom` self-registers automatically.

## Global Rules
- Do not install packages without confirming first
- Do not use `setState` for app state
- Do not put business logic in views
- Do not use `BuildContext` in controllers or services
- Never recreate primitives from `core/`
- Atom variables use no suffix: `final isSelected = Atom(false)` not `final isSelectedAtom`
- Never use `print()` — use `debugLog()`

## Workflow
- Read existing files before editing — never assume file contents
- For tasks with 3+ steps, write a plan first
- After any correction, log the pattern in `tasks/lessons.md`
- Never mark a task complete without verifying it runs
